00:43:08.930 --> 00:43:11.180
SPEAKER: Well, we have about
10 minutes for questions.

00:43:11.180 --> 00:43:13.680
We'll go with the hard half one
finish if you have meetings.

00:43:13.680 --> 00:43:15.020
I will kick off with a question.

00:43:15.020 --> 00:43:17.212
What is your
opinion on big tech?

00:43:17.212 --> 00:43:18.920
So if you think that
Amazon, for example,

00:43:18.920 --> 00:43:21.230
is taking a huge amount
of consumer dollars,

00:43:21.230 --> 00:43:23.300
what's your opinion on
that and perhaps where

00:43:23.300 --> 00:43:25.097
that might lead
us in the future?

00:43:25.097 --> 00:43:27.263
And if you have a question,
please put your hand up.

00:43:27.263 --> 00:43:29.570
DHARSHINI DAVID: As in
whether it's a force for good?

00:43:29.570 --> 00:43:33.380
SPEAKER: Yes, and perhaps
comparable to nation states,

00:43:33.380 --> 00:43:36.140
for example, if you think
how much Amazon has compared

00:43:36.140 --> 00:43:38.404
with smaller GDP countries.

00:43:38.404 --> 00:43:39.320
DHARSHINI DAVID: Sure.

00:43:39.320 --> 00:43:40.861
It's a bit like the
dollar, isn't it?

00:43:40.861 --> 00:43:43.370
It has traversed nation states.

00:43:43.370 --> 00:43:44.480
Is it a force for good?

00:43:47.240 --> 00:43:49.460
Basically what it does
is epitomizes the way

00:43:49.460 --> 00:43:51.510
our global economy
is changing, and it

00:43:51.510 --> 00:43:54.330
epitomizes all these
forces of globalization.

00:43:54.330 --> 00:43:57.620
We're all using consumer power
to get the American dream

00:43:57.620 --> 00:44:01.520
on the cheap, and
we all want that.

00:44:01.520 --> 00:44:02.690
What are you sacrificing?

00:44:02.690 --> 00:44:05.660
You're sacrificing
perhaps the things

00:44:05.660 --> 00:44:08.960
that we've come to hold
dear-- things like employment

00:44:08.960 --> 00:44:10.290
practices and things like that.

00:44:10.290 --> 00:44:11.900
So I think if you're looking
at Amazon in particular,

00:44:11.900 --> 00:44:12.942
there's pros and cons.

00:44:12.942 --> 00:44:15.150
It's a bit like making
America great again, isn't it?

00:44:15.150 --> 00:44:16.816
You can buy cheap,
but there is a price.

